## Following Streams

Right-click any packet → Follow → TCP Stream / HTTP Stream / UDP Stream

This reassembles the full conversation into readable text. Very useful for:
- Reading HTTP requests and responses
- Seeing FTP file transfers
- Reading cleartext credentials

---

## Exporting Objects

Extract files transferred over the network:

Go to **File → Export Objects → HTTP** (or SMB, FTP, TFTP)

This lets you save images, documents, and scripts transmitted in the capture.

---

## Statistics

**Statistics → Protocol Hierarchy**
Shows breakdown of all protocols in the capture — great first step.

**Statistics → Conversations**
Shows all TCP/UDP conversations — useful for spotting unusual connections.

**Statistics → Endpoints**
Lists all IP addresses seen in the capture.

**Statistics → IO Graph**
Plots packet rate over time — spike = burst of activity.

